## Feature: User / Role Info Panel at Bottom of Sidebar

### Context
Add connected user identity and role information at the bottom of the left collapsible sidebar, visible across all pages that use the shared `_sidebar_nav.html` partial. In collapsed mode only the person icon is shown; expanded mode shows email + role badge(s).

### Changes

1. **`src/front/templates/partials/layout/_sidebar_nav.html`** — Appended a `sidebar-user` footer block inside the `{% if sidebar_menu %}` guard. Uses `get_user_email()`, `get_user_role()`, and `get_user_domain_role()` Jinja2 globals to display the connected user's email and role badges (Admin badge in red, domain role in blue when it differs from the app role).
2. **`src/front/static/global/css/sidebar-layout.css`** — Added `display: flex; flex-direction: column;` to `.sidebar-nav` so `margin-top: auto` on `.sidebar-user` pins the panel to the bottom. Added full `.sidebar-user`, `.sidebar-user-info`, `.sidebar-user-icon`, `.sidebar-user-details`, `.sidebar-user-email`, `.sidebar-user-badges`, and `.sidebar-role-badge` rules. Added collapsed-state overrides that hide the text/badges and center the icon.

### Modified Files
- `src/front/templates/partials/layout/_sidebar_nav.html`
- `src/front/static/global/css/sidebar-layout.css`

### Test Results
- Pure UI/CSS change; no logic affected. Existing test suite unaffected.

