## Remove: Role Badge from Navbar

### Context
Now that the user's role is shown in the sidebar user footer, the redundant role pill in the top-right navbar is removed.

### Changes

1. **`src/front/templates/base.html`** — `#roleNavBadgeItem` marked `d-none` and `aria-hidden="true"`; stripped the icon/label content to leave only the stub needed by JS.
2. **`src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css`** — Collapsed the two `#roleNavBadgeItem` rules into one that keeps the element `display: none !important` even after `permissions.js` adds the `.is-visible` class.

### Modified Files
- `src/front/templates/base.html`
- `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css`

### Test Results
- Pure UI/CSS change. JS still runs without errors (guards with `if (!item) return`). Existing test suite unaffected.
